      <title>Re: Evolving Items vs Rec Level</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Veterans&amp;message.id=213068#M213068</link>
      <description>Naw, just use recommended levels on the evolving items.  If you level the item too fast, the stats still have the lower red numbers that will increase as you gain in level.  With the sheer number of kills needed to level a piece of evolving gear, you should be leveling both yourself and the item at a steady pace.  The nice part about many of the evolving items is that in the end, you would have a piece of gear that you would want to use a good ways above the recommended level, thereby increasing its usefulness and shelf life.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
