      <description>It's a best-guess, but I think the issue is about how they would evolve at lower levels.  Equip a level 35 with an evolving wepon, give them a DS, a Temp and dump them in a zone with all light/dark blue mobs, the speed of evolution would be silly.  Adjusting the evolution curve accoring to level would take unneccesary additional code and might just screw anyone truying to level one genuinely at 35.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Yes, to some degree recommended levels would seem to redres this imbalance, except that you can give it to your 60-70 after it's evolved. Thus, all evolving items would need to become Attuneable by default if Recommended levels were to be used instead of Required levels.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Even so, this is clearly not how evolving items were intended to be used, req levels are fine, and even then i feel they ought to be attuneable to start levelling them.&lt;br&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
